interface

typescript

(1) allows to define type separately
    - only for objects
    - alternatively: alias
        - to apply custom-name for type
        - also for primitives
(2) may be implemented by class

EXAMPLE
type Point = { x: number; y: number };

interface Shape {
     center: Point;
}

class Circle implements Shape {
    center: Point;
    radius: number;

    constructor(center: Point, radius: number = 2) {
        this.center = center;
        this.radius = radius;
    }
}

console.log(new Circle({x: 2, y: 3})); // Circle { center: { x: 2, y: 3 }, radius: 2 }

